  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 26 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1480 mg
---

In a #medium pot{}, combine @Basmati Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Core, deseed, and dice @Bell Pepper{1} into 1-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and finely dice @Onion{1}. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Roughly chop @Cilantro{1/4%oz}. Thinly slice @Chili Pepper{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and onion; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> If needed, add a splash of water to help pepper and onion soften.

Stir in garlic; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wash out pan.

While veggies cook, pat @Shrimp{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Place chicken in a #medium bowl{} and toss with @Yogurt{2%tbsp}, @Garam Masala{1/2%tsp}, salt, and pepper until evenly coated.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned all over, ~{2-4%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step). Reduce heat to medium.

> Rinse shrimp under cold water, then pat dry with paper towels. Swap in shrimp for chicken.

To the same pan, stir in @Curry Sauce Base{5%oz}, @Paprika{1%tsp}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, 1/2 cup water (for 4 servings), @Butter{1%tbsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to low. Cook until sauce is thickened and chicken is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> If sauce seems too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Add veggies and @Sour Cream{1.5%tbsp}; stir to combine. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Divide between shallow bowls or plates.

Top with chicken and sauce. Sprinkle with cilantro and sliced chili if desired. Serve.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.